<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-60-0573 </DOCNO><TEXT>Offers an up-to-date overview of the major activities in the field andappraises the principles involved in applying biotechnological techniquesto environmental problems. coverage includes pollution of agriculturalland, techniques of treating effluents, environmental problems causedby solid waste disposal in landfill sites, and the potential for biogasgeneration at such sites. It also examines the potential uses and dangersof future technologies in environmental management, such as manipulatingaromatic-degrading microorganisms, use of recalcitrant xenobiotics, biologicalpest control, and controlling biological nitrogen fixation.</TEXT></DOC>